---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = '/penzana-del-merel';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Our Story — La Penzana del Merel"
  description="The history of La Penzana del Merel: from the Trattoria Cima Verde in 1959 to today's family pizzeria. Three generations, a century-old chestnut tree, and Bergamo roots."
  lang="en"
  currentPath={`${base}/en/history/`}
>

  <section class="hero" style="padding-block:clamp(3rem,8vw,5rem);">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">History</span>
      <h1>The Roots of Merel</h1>
      <p>From the 1936 acquisition to today's pizzeria: three generations, a century-old chestnut tree, and the pride of staying true to oneself.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:780px;">

      <div style="display:flex; gap:0.75rem; margin-bottom:2.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
        {[
          { year: '1936', label: 'Acquisition' },
          { year: '1959', label: 'Inn opens' },
          { year: '1989', label: 'Naples pizza finalist' },
          { year: "1990s", label: 'Transformed into pizzeria' },
          { year: 'Today', label: 'Third generation' },
        ].map(ev => (
          <div style="background:var(--bg-warm); border-radius:var(--radius); padding:0.6rem 1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--accent-gold);">
            <div style="font-size:0.7rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--stone);">{ev.label}</div>
            <div style="font-family:var(--font-display); font-weight:700; font-size:1.05rem; color:var(--green-deep);">{ev.year}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2>1936 — The Building</h2>
      <figure class="storia-img reveal" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <img src={`${base}/img/trattoria_alpina_historical_photo.png`} alt="Historical photo: Orezzo - Trattoria Alpina, the original building with water reflection" loading="lazy" style="width:100%; border-radius:var(--radius-lg); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm);" />
        <figcaption style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:0.5rem; font-style:italic;">Orezzo — Trattoria Alpina, the original building</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>The building was acquired in 1936 by <strong>Alessandro Merelli</strong>. Rented out for a few decades, it remained a reference point in the hamlet of Orezzo.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">31 December 1959 — The Inn Opens</h2>
      <p>On the last day of the year, <strong>Tarcisio</strong>, Alessandro's son, opens the inn as <em>Trattoria Cima Verde</em>. From the very start it stands out for its <strong>genuine character</strong>: a place for relaxed summer afternoons with a glass of red at the counter and bowls under the shade of the century-old <strong>chestnut tree</strong>.</p>

      <blockquote class="pullquote">
        Glasses of red, bowls on the lawn, the shade of the old chestnut. A place where time still had the right to slow down.
      </blockquote>

      <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">1989 — A Passion for the Oven</h2>
      <p>Tarcisio develops a passion for <strong>building bread ovens</strong>. The turning point comes in 1989, when he is a <strong>finalist at the Naples Centenary of the Margherita pizza</strong> — an extraordinary recognition for a craftsman from Bergamo.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">1990s — La Penzana del Merel</h2>
      <p>With the help of his son <strong>Efrem</strong> and daughter-in-law <strong>Laura Merla</strong>, Tarcisio transforms the inn into a <strong>pizzeria</strong>. The three name it <em>La Penzana del Merel</em> — evoking the simple tin-roofed shelters where local farmers used to store their <em>rastei e furchine</em> (rakes and pitchforks). A name that smells of soil and authentic Bergamo.</p>
      <p>From the earliest years, their pizzas — crafted with care in every detail — attract many people from Bergamo looking for a cool spot in summer or a rustic hillside setting for festive days and evenings out.</p>

      <blockquote class="pullquote">
        "La Penzana del Merel" — the tin-roofed shelters where farmers kept their rakes and pitchforks. A name rooted in the land.
      </blockquote>

      <figure class="storia-img reveal" style="margin-top:2rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <img src={`${base}/img/general_pizza_overview.png`} alt="Freshly baked pizzas from the wood-fired oven" loading="lazy" style="width:100%; border-radius:var(--radius-lg); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm);" />
        <figcaption style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:0.5rem; font-style:italic;">Penzana pizzas — crafted with care in every detail</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">Today</h2>
      <p>Believing that the present is what tomorrow will be history, the family wants to continue this story as positively as they have over the last fifty years.</p>
      <p style="font-style:italic; font-family:var(--font-display); font-size:1.1rem; color:var(--green-deep);">"We want to change in order to remain ourselves, to remain with you."<br/><span style="font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; font-family:var(--font-body); color:var(--stone);">— The Merel family</span></p>

      <div style="margin-top:3rem; display:flex; gap:1rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href={`${base}/en/family/`} class="btn btn-green">The family today</a>
        <a href={`${base}/en/menu/`} class="btn btn-outline" style="color:var(--green-deep); border-color:var(--stone-xlight);">See the menu</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


</BaseLayout>
